name: Choked Palindrome
description:
No one knew about her. Tiny enough that the length of the foot fit in my palm, she easily got into a small box, which I threw deep into the closet. One day I told my friend about it. Frankness didn't make it any easier, but in the end she just suffocated in her cardboard sarcophagus — time turned out to be stronger than my apathetic longing.

Decomposed as much as the pain of unrequited attraction can decompose, she turned into a handful of dust, since then occasionally glistening in the thick darkness of the past.
